mesquite.lib

Class MesquiteDouble

  • java.lang.Object
    • mesquite.lib.MesquiteDouble
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Listable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MesquiteParameter

    public class MesquiteDouble
extends java.lang.Object
implements Listable
    This double wrapper class is used to be able to pass doubles by reference and have the original change as needed

      • lessThan

        public static boolean lessThan(double value1,
                               double value2,
                               double toleranceProportion)
        Returns true if value 1 is less than value 2. Its response is conservative by a proportional tolerance as given (i.e., if tolerance is 0.01, then this returns false even if value1 is greater than or equal to value 2, as long as the difference between value1 and value2 is less than 1% of the larger of the absolute values of value1 and value2

      • greaterThan

Its response is conservative by a proportional tolerance as given (i.e., if tolerance is 0.01, then this returns false even if value1 is less than or equal to value 2, as long as the difference between value1 and value2 is less than 1% of the larger of the absolute values of value1 and value2

      • greaterThanByFactor

        public static boolean greaterThanByFactor(double value1,
                                          double value2,
                                          double factor)
        Returns true if value 1 is greater than value 2 by at least the factor given. Its response is conservative by a proportional tolerance as given (i.e., if tolerance is 0.01, then this returns false even if value1 is less than or equal to value 2, as long as the difference between value1 and value2 is less than 1% of the larger of the absolute values of value1 and value2
